[
    {
        "content": "<p>I was just reading <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semiring#Star_semirings\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semiring#Star_semirings</a>. Is a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/star_ring\">docs#star_ring</a> a star semiring in that sense? It seems not <span aria-label=\"frown\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f641\" role=\"img\" title=\"frown\">:frown:</span></p>",
        "id": 317364037,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1671715370
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/*-algebra\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/*-algebra</a> has no mention of *-semirings</p>",
        "id": 317365343,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1671715775
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This seems like an unfortunate name clash. Any thoughts on this? Context is <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/pull/17965\">#17965</a></p>",
        "id": 317365521,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1671715824
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://hackage.haskell.org/package/semirings\">https://hackage.haskell.org/package/semirings</a> seems to agree with wikipedia on the use of *-semiring</p>",
        "id": 317365659,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1671715872
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm thinking maybe name everything <code>kstar</code> instead of  <code>star</code> when it's about the Kleene star.</p>",
        "id": 317365662,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1671715873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At the very least we need to change the documentation of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/has_star.star\">docs#has_star.star</a> to not claim that we are using star-semirings, or at least clarify the confusion</p>",
        "id": 317365895,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1671715937
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I will cross-reference the Wikipedia pages too.</p>",
        "id": 317365969,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1671715963
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Don't forget to forward-port the doc fix</p>",
        "id": 317366023,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1671715979
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I my personal opinion the use of <code>star</code> we currently have is the most used in mathematics.</p>",
        "id": 317366180,
        "sender_full_name": "Riccardo Brasca",
        "timestamp": 1671716029
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, except that seemingly half the people using the API don't like calling it <code>star</code> and use <code>conj</code> as the name instead</p>",
        "id": 317366842,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1671716235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It seems pretty clear to me that the Kleene stuff is much more specialized and should get a longer name.</p>",
        "id": 317383282,
        "sender_full_name": "Patrick Massot",
        "timestamp": 1671720560
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Agreed. I'm settling on <code>kstar</code> for now.</p>",
        "id": 317408435,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1671727842
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's nice because for those that know about Kleene stars they'll realise that this is what it is</p>",
        "id": 317414274,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1671729538
    }
]